BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260512T093000
DTEND:20260512T170000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.939ft at 09:30\n-2.977ft at 17:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 <strong>Dawn to 10:00AM:</strong> Holding blend of long-period SSW Souther
 n Hemi and shorter-period NW/WNW swell mix keeps many spots in waist-chest
  high+ waves\, as summertime standouts see sets going a foot+ overhead on 
 favorable tide. Light/variable winds through the morning.\n\n<strong>After
 noon Outlook:</strong> Wave size holds. Winds turning light+ SW onshore fo
 r some texture. Late afternoon/evening high tide bogs down tide sensitive 
 spots. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260513T060600
DTEND:20260513T064200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.526ft at 06:06\n-2.951ft at 06:42\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Easing mix of SSW Southern Hemi and NW/WNW swell for mainly thigh to stoma
 ch high surf\, as top spots hit shoulder high+. Tide sensitive spots will 
 be slowed by mid morning high tide\, then ebbing tide helps through mid da
 y. \n\nLight/variable winds due much of the morning\, go light SW mid day\
 , then  offshore NW flow expected later afternoon into the evening. 
END:VEVENT
